# Godot Logging Addendum

`godot-run.sh` captures the broadest runtime surface because it tees Godot stdout even when the in-game sinks do not flush cleanly.

Partial coverage limits:
- Editor-launched play sessions do not flow through `scripts/godot-run.sh`, so only the in-process `user://logs/*.log` sinks are available there.
- Hard crashes before `NOTIFICATION_WM_CLOSE_REQUEST` can prevent the `user://` sinks from flushing.
- When that happens, `.buildrunner/godot.log` from `scripts/godot-run.sh` is the primary crash artifact.
